If a lab wants to use a cloned tissue sample (e.g., skin graft), that sample is physically separate and not connected to the live neural network. It has its own independent identity (a different key). The network has a one‑way trust: the lab clone can be used to authenticate that the sample came from Chase, but the live network never accepts commands from the clone.

