1. Latency in RF Communication Between Nodes
Typical latency figures (within Chase’s body mesh):

Transmission One‑way latency Medium Notes
Head node → chest node (direct RF) < 1 ms 10.245 GHz Skin‑surface propagation, < 50 cm distance
Limb node → spine node (through body) 2–5 ms 10.23‑10.30 GHz Signal passes through tissue; slight delay due to dielectric absorption
